    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've created:\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**5 files — 4 new, 1 modified — following the exact `next/server` / `user-agent.ts` patterns.**\n\n### New Files\n\n1. **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** — Pure TypeScript, no external deps:\n   - `Geo` interface (7 optional string fields)\n   - `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries: US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA)\n   - `geoFromHeaders(headers)` — reads Vercel headers, falls back to `cf-ipcountry` (Cloudflare) for `countryCode`, derives `country` name from map; uses `?? undefined` to convert `null` returns from `headers.get()`\n   - `geo({ headers })` — thin wrapper delegating to `geoFromHeaders`\n   - `isInRegion(geo, regions[])` — case-insensitive `countryCode` membership check\n   - `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2)` — Haversine formula, returns km\n\n2. **`packages/next/geo.js`** — CommonJS entry point mirroring `server.js`: `geoExports` object + explicit `exports.fn = geoExports.fn` for CJS/ESM interop\n\n3. **`packages/next/geo.d.ts`** — Type declarations mirroring `server.d.ts`: re-exports `Geo` type + all 4 functions from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`\n\n4. **`packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** — Jest tests co-located with source (like `adapters/headers.test.ts`), covering all functions including NYC→London ≈5570km±50 distance check\n\n### Modified File\n\n5. **`packages/next/package.json`** — Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` in `files` array after `\"form.d.ts\"` / before `\"router.js\"` (alphabetical: g between f and r)",
